We create a table of values:

| $x$ | $f(x) = x^2 - 4$ | Point |
| $-3$ | $9 - 4 = 5$ | $(-3, 5)$ |
| $-2$ | $4 - 4 = 0$ | $(-2, 0)$ |
| $-1$ | $1 - 4 = -3$ | $(-1, -3)$ |
| $0$ | $0 - 4 = -4$ | $(0, -4)$ |
| $1$ | $1 - 4 = -3$ | $(1, -3)$ |
| $2$ | $4 - 4 = 0$ | $(2, 0)$ |
| $3$ | $9 - 4 = 5$ | $(3, 5)$ |

Plotting these points and connecting them with a smooth curve gives the 
parabola:

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.6]
 (-4,0) – (4,0) node[right] {$x$};
 (0,-5) – (0,6) node[above] {$y$};
 plot (, { - 4});
 in {-3,-2,-1,1,2,3} (,0.15) – (,-0.15) node[below] {$\x$};
 in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4,5} (0.15,) – (-0.15,);
 at (-0.2, -4) {$-4$};
 at (-0.2, 5) {$5$};
 lldraw[AtlasTeal] (-3,5) circle (2pt);
 lldraw[AtlasTeal] (-2,0) circle (2pt);
 lldraw[AtlasTeal] (-1,-3) circle (2pt);
 lldraw[AtlasTeal] (0,-4) circle (2pt);
 lldraw[AtlasTeal] (1,-3) circle (2pt);
 lldraw[AtlasTeal] (2,0) circle (2pt);
 lldraw[AtlasTeal] (3,5) circle (2pt);
tikzpicture
center

content.problem:
Determine whether each curve represents a function.

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.55]
 % Graph (a): parabola - IS a function
 scope
 (-2.5,0) – (3,0) node[right] {$x$};
 (0,-0.5) – (0,4.5) node[above] {$y$};
 plot (, {0.5*(-0.5)^2 + 0.5});
 (1,-0.3) – (1,4);
 at (0.25, -1.2) {**(a)**};
 scope

 % Graph (b): circle - NOT a function
 scope[xshift=7cm]
 (-2.5,0) – (2.5,0) node[right] {$x$};
 (0,-2.5) – (0,2.5) node[above] {$y$};
 (0,0) circle (1.5);
 (0.8,-2.2) – (0.8,2.2);
 lldraw[AtlasRose] (0.8, 1.27) circle (2.5pt);
 lldraw[AtlasRose] (0.8, -1.27) circle (2.5pt);
 at (0, -3) {**(b)**};
 scope

 % Graph (c): S-curve - IS a function
 scope[xshift=14cm]
 (-2.5,0) – (3,0) node[right] {$x$};
 (0,-2) – (0,2.5) node[above] {$y$};

 plot (, {0.4*(-0.5)^3});
 (1.5,-1.8) – (1.5,2.2);
 at (0.25, -2.7) {**(c)**};
 scope
tikzpicture
center

